<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2637501>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Pholoicola chambersae gen. et sp. nov. A, adult female with 3 males attached, ventral; B, female, dorsal; C, detached egg sac; D, adult male, lateral view showing position of developing paired spermatophores; E, adult male, ventral; F, cephalothorax of male, lateral view showing thickened frontal region and clawed limb; G, spermatophore; H, last male copepodid stage, antennule; I, antenna; J, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm, B–C, 250 µm, D–E, 50 µm, F–H, 25 µm, I–J 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2637501/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

